Miners at Spain's state-owned Hullerasdel Norte S.A. (Hunosa) coal company have called a 72-hourstrike starting on Monday to protest against a restructuringplan that entails layoffs, union sources said.    They said more stoppages would follow in coming weeks.    The unions rejected a company compromise proposal to extendthe period of the restructuring plan to four years instead oftwo and said there should be no job losses.    The company wants to shed some 2,000 jobs and start cuttingback on production to help boost productivity by five pctyearly to the year 2000.&#3;